text: Chesterfield County is a county in the U.S. state of Virginia. As of the 2020 census, 364,548 people lived there. Its county seat is Chesterfield Court House. It was recognized as a county on May 25, 1749. == References == == Other websites == * * Category:1740s establishments in Virginia Category:1749 establishments Category:Virginia counties
